headline: Norwegian Cruise Line (NCLH): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: What a time it’s been for Norwegian Cruise Line. In the past six months alone, the company’s stock price has increased by a massive 57.3%, reaching $26.60 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the performance may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
